Make the backplane wiring more flexible.
  3 positions for the IDE card(s) provides space to install HD
  4 positions for the SR4 card

1)
 Remove wire 1A28 - 4C23
 Remove wire 4C23 - 5C23
 Place wire  7C23 > 8C23
 Place wire  1A28 > 5C23
 Place wire  3C23 > 4C23
 Place wire  3C28 > 4A28

   Slot:  Card:
      0   MM3
      1   MON
      2   HD or IDE0
      3   IDE0 or IDE1 or GPP or RAM
      4   IDE1 or GPP or RAM
      5   SR4 or US4 or GPP or RAM
      6   SR4 or US4 or GPP or RAM
      7   SR4 or US4 or GPP or RAM
      8   SR4 or GPP or RAM
      9   IOP or GPP or RAM

Jumper for 3 SR4 cards with IOP or IDE for FLEX

2)
 Remove wire AC3 - DC23 
 Place a 3-pin jumper on DC23,
 bend the outer pins and place the center pin in the DC23 hole.

  Slot: D      C     B
         _
 AC3  __| |
        | |
        |*| < DC23
 CC23 __| |
        }_|

 Place a piece of insulation under the bent pins.
       
 Place wire AC3 > one side jumper 
 Place wire CC23 > other side jumnper

  Jumper select
   Slot:  Jumper: Card:
      D      CC23   US4 or SR4
      D      AC3    IDE
 